              </div>
              <div class='span8'>
                <h3>Key concepts</h3>
                <p>
                  We'll give you the big picture, so you can place each of the technical practices we'll show you in context. You'll come away understanding the why as well as the how.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class='row-fluid'>
              <div class='span4 pull-center'>
                <i class='icon-beaker enormous-icon circled pull-center'></i>
              </div>
              <div class='span8'>
                <h3>Experiment</h3>
                <p>
                  The course gives you the opportunity to experiment with tools in a safe environment, put together something end-to-end in a short time, and investigate the effects and benefits of CD.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            </hr>
          </li>
          <li class='span6'>
            <div class='row-fluid'>
              <div class='span4 pull-center'>
                <i class='icon-cogs enormous-icon circled pull-center'></i>
              </div>
              <div class='span8'>
                <h3>Putting Tools Together</h3>
                <p>
                  Different tool serve different purposes. We'll look at the different types, and put a selection together to form a deployment pipeline that is more than the sum of its parts.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div class='row-fluid'>
              <div class='span4 pull-center'>
                <i class='icon-briefcase enormous-icon circled pull-center'></i>
              </div>
              <div class='span8'>
                <h3>Carrying Legacy Baggage?</h3>
                <p>
                  You're probably working on existing projects rather than starting shiny new ones. We'll show you
                  pragmatic steps to start introducing CD techniques on an existing application.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            </hr>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
